               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors; groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I-1 and I-4; sometimes the first word of Text I-5;  incipit of (sub)sections partly section numbers of Text I-4; elements of the punctuation signs and of text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-2 is followed by the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam wäladitä ʾamlak ... "O my Lady Mary, Godbearing ..." (fol. 7ra-7ra l.11)</note>
                     <note>- ʾƎgzǝʾtǝyä ʾǝmmu lä-ʾǝgziʾǝyä kähali ... "My Lady, Mother of my Lord the Almighty ..." (fol. 7ra l.11-rb l.3) (cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- Sälam läki Maryam ʾǝmmä mädḫǝn wä nädd ... "Salutation to you Mary, Mother of the Saviour, Mother of the Flame ..." (fol. 7rb l.3-7vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Mary (Text I-4) are numbered, partly in a secondary hand (the same as Additio 1).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
