                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#8vb">Fol. 8vb</locus>: Supplication for the donor.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The supplication is written in Amharic, in purple pen. The donor's baptismal name, Gäbrä ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer, and names of his family members are included in the note.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#131va">Fol. 131va</locus>: Purchase note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that the "book of ʿAddi Qiyahto" was purchased by Wäldä Yoḥannǝs during the time of King Mǝnilǝk II (r. 1889-1913) and the governor šum ʾagame Dästa whose baptismal name is Gäbrä Ḥǝywät (in office 1902-08). 
Wäldä Yoḥannǝs' family members are also mentioned (e.g., father: Wäldä ʾAbbǝyä ʾƎgziʾ, mother: Wälättä Maryam).
A similar note is written in purple pen on fol. 2v.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Space left for the rubricated incipit of the 114th miracle is not filled on fol. 130va.&#xD;
- Omitted words are inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 23rb, 25rb, 67vb, 81rb, 97ra, 112rb.&#xD;
- Erasures: fols. 3vb, 4ra, 5ra, 93va (several lines). &#xD;
- Many corrections and omitted passages are written interlineally or in the margins on fols. 3va-8r, in purple pen. &#xD;
- Mistaken letters are marked in purple pen: e.g., fols. 17va, 18ra, 19vb, 78va, 81vb, 119vb.&#xD;
- Short list of names (rulers and authorities) is crudely written in pencil on fol. 131vb.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
